data.summary: Bonhams London to Brighton Veteran Car Run
data.description: Bonhams London to Brighton Veteran Car Run, which sees owners of pre-1905 veteran cars drive 60 miles from London to Brighton. The world's longest-running motoring event takes place annually on the first Sunday in November, and commemorates the Emancipation Run of 14 Nov 1896 which celebrated the passing into law of the Locomotives on the Highway Act, which raised the speed limit for 'light locomotives' from four to 14 mph and abolished the requirement for vehicles to be preceded by a man on foot waving a red flag. The event often attracts celebrity car enthusiasts
data.organisation: London to Brighton Veteran Car Run

data.summary: KSI v Logan Paul turn pro for boxing rematch in Los Angeles
data.description: YouTube influencers KSI and Logan Paul face each other in a professional boxing match in Los Angeles following their August 2018 amateur debut in Manchester, which ended in a majority draw. The 2018 fight's livestream on YouTube's pay-per-view service drew over one million viewers, making it the largest non-professional boxing match of all time in terms of paying viewers. The rematch is streamed live on DAZN. Although the first fight was amateur, the pair turn pro for this rematch, removing the headgear they wore for their 2018 bout * KSI initially challenged Logan to a fight after the latter caused widespread controversy for posting a video in which he happens upon a suspected suicide in a Japanese forest
data.venue: STAPLES Center, 1111 S Figueroa St, Los Angeles, CA

data.summary: World's first museum of the vagina launches with VIP opening party
data.description: VIP launch party held for The Vagina Museum, the world's first physical museum dedicated to the gynaecological anatomy, ahead of its public grand opening tomorrow. Situated in London's Camden Market, the museum launches with the exhibition 'Muff Busters: Vagina Myths and How to Fight Them', exploring myths and misconceptions about the vagina. The free museum was started by director Florence Schechter as a pop-up in March 2017 after she discovered Iceland has a Penis Museum, but there was no female equivalent anywhere in the world. The permanent extension has been established after a crowdfunding campaign raised almost £50k from supporters around the world. An outreach programme is expected to support healthy and inclusive sex and relationship education in association with doctors and other medical professionals. The museum is also available to hire for private parties * An online Vagina Museum was founded in Austria in 2014

The permanent extension has been established after a crowdfunding campaign raised almost £50k from supporters around the world. An outreach programme is expected to support healthy and inclusive sex and relationship education in association with doctors and other medical professionals.
